snippet: Just as in the 2000 presidential election, the results of Florida’s voting were still up in the air the day after Election Day. The difference is that in 2012 it doesn’t matter.
abstract: Florida remains too close to call one day after Pres Barack Obama was reelected to a second term; unlike in 2000, however, when balance of election hung on Florida's results, state's choice is an afterthought in 2012.
lead_paragraph: Just as in the 2000 presidential election, the results of Florida’s voting were still up in the air the day after Election Day. The difference is that in 2012 it doesn’t matter.

headline.seo: Florida’s Votes Unclaimed, but Less Depends on Them
headline.main: Florida’s Votes Go Unclaimed, but This Time Less Depends on Them
